deselectGroup(25.10)                                      deselectGroup(25.10)

Name
       deselectGroup - Deselects a group

Syntax
        deselectGroup

       <groupName>

       [-help]

       Deselects a group. Use this command after selecting a group.

Parameters
       <groupName>
              Specifies the name of the group.

              Data_type: string, required

       -help  Outputs  a  brief description that includes the type and default
              information for each deselectGroup parameter. For a detailed de-
              scription of the command and all of

              its parameters, use the man command:

              man deselectGroup

Related Information
              * selectGroup

              * Floorplanning the Design chapter in the Innovus User Guide

